subject: .Ah .Awe and .Ox
msgSnippet: Hello, I m new to Quickscript, but it appears to me that in the General American accent, the three letters .Ah, .Awe, and .Ox are pronunced in exactly the same
messageBody:
Hello,

I'm new to Quickscript, but it appears to me that in the General American accent, the three letters .Ah, .Awe, and .Ox are pronunced in exactly the same way. Being phonetic, would Quickscript allow a writer with a General American accent to write all three sounds the same way? If so, which letter would be used?

Thanks,
Justin
